  "prompt": "What exactly is the vijay mallya case?",
  "response": "The Vijay Mallya case is a high-profile legal and financial scandal involving Indian businessman Vijay Mallya. Mallya, once known as the \"King of Good Times\" due to his lavish lifestyle and involvement in the liquor and aviation industries, faced numerous charges related to financial mismanagement and fraud.\n\nKey points of the case include:\n\n1. **Business Ventures**: Mallya was the chairman of United Breweries Group and founded Kingfisher Airlines. The airline, despite its initial success, faced severe financial difficulties and was grounded in 2012.\n\n2. **Loan Defaults**: Kingfisher Airlines accumulated significant debt, leading to defaults on loans taken from various Indian banks. Mallya was accused of defaulting on loans worth approximately \u20b99,000 crore (around $1.3 billion).\n\n3. **Legal Actions**: Indian authorities, including the Enforcement Directorate (ED) and the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI), launched investigations into Mallya's financial dealings. He was charged with money laundering, financial fraud, and siphoning off funds meant for Kingfisher Airlines.\n\n4. **Escape and Extradition**: In 2016, Mallya left India and moved to the United Kingdom, prompting Indian authorities to seek his extradition. In 2018, a UK court ruled in favor of extraditing Mallya to India to face charges, but various legal proceedings and appeals have delayed his return.\n\n5. **Current Status**: As of the latest updates, Mallya remains in the UK, fighting extradition. He has been declared a fugitive economic offender in India, and his assets have been seized by Indian authorities to recover the loan amounts.\n\nThe case symbolizes issues of corporate governance, financial accountability, and the challenges in bringing high-profile economic offenders to justice. It has also sparked debates on the efficacy of legal and regulatory frameworks in dealing with large-scale financial frauds in India.",
